  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a design-space value for a single variable font axis, identified by its four-byte tag.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` specifies a single axis value for a variable font, pairing a four-byte axis tag with a design-space coordinate. Use a collection of these with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.VariationDesignPosition> or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate})> to select a specific variation instance.

## Examples

```csharp
var coordinates = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700f },
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth"), Value = 75f }
};

using var typeface = originalTypeface.Clone(coordinates);
```
]]></format></remarks>
